text: I am full of stories.
Pick one. I dare you.
Shall I tell you about my uncle,
Whose life is a test?
Shall I tell you about my cousin,
Whose palace is unfinished?
Or shall I tell you of the stars,
Why they respond to you so slowly?
I am full of stories
And there is only so much time.
Shall I tell you about the boy who dreams the world?
Shall I tell you about the land which people rush to cross?
I am full of stories.
Picking one is like picking a star out of the clear night sky.
Shall I tell you about my love?
She is near to me always.
Shall I tell you of my water
Which is getting thirsty?
Perhaps I should save you the time and tell you
That the whole world is determined to become my family
But what else have you got?
I am full of stories
Shall I tell you about my sister?
Let me tell you about my sister...
